  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "1.  Knowledge and skills of health workers in preparing for and responding to disaster situations enhanced at all levels.\r\n2.  Measures for strengthening hospitals so that they may function in emergencies implemented.\r\n3.  Emergency contingency plans developed in key districts to prepare for various types of disasters.\r\n4.  Best practices in health disaster management identified and disseminate.\r\n6.  Strong mechanisms for health sector coordination and rapid response through enhanced information management at central, regional and district level in place.\r\n7.  Minimum standing readiness to respond to emergencies strengthened and response promptly.\r\n8.  Disagregated data collected for better planning.\r\n9.  Promotion for rights based approaces to health."
    },
    "ne": null
  },
